function onTick() arm = input.getBool(1) -- ARM tgt = input.getBool(2) -- Valid Target ammo = input.getBool(3) -- Ammo blink = input.getBool(4) -- Blinker depl = input.getBool(5) -- Deployed man = input.getBool(6) --Manual Control
r = 0 b = 0
if depl then g = 1 -- When unarmed, skips if man then b = 1 elseif arm then r = 1 g = 0.5 b = 0 -- When out of ammo if not ammo then if blink then r = 1 g = 1 else r = 0 g = 0 end -- When found a valid target elseif tgt then g = 0 end end else g = 0 end
output.setNumber(1, r) -- R output.setNumber(2, g) -- G output.setNumber(3, b) -- B end

min = 25 max = 500
-- Searches for the first target, which is in a valid range function onTick()
min = input.getNumber(4) max = input.getNumber(8)
tgt = false last_dist = max
for i = 1, 8 do if input.getBool(1) then -- Target found dist = input.getNumber(i*4-3) if dist < last_dist and dist < max and dist > min then -- Target within valid range (meaning closest tgt, within min and max) tgt = true azim = input.getNumber(i*4-2) elev = input.getNumber(i*4-1) last_dist = dist end end end
if tgt then output.setBool(1, true) output.setNumber(1, dist) output.setNumber(2, azim) output.setNumber(3, elev) end end

targets = {}
function onTick() man = input.getBool(9) --Manual Control arm = input.getBool(10) dep = input.getBool(11) blink = input.getBool(12)
hdg = input.getNumber(4) elv = input.getNumber(8) fov = 2*40^input.getNumber(12) rng = input.getNumber(16)
--Collects radar targets targets = {} for i = 1, 8 do if input.getBool(i) then targets[i] = {dist = input.getNumber(4*i-3), az =input.getNumber(4*i-2), elv = input.getNumber(4*i-1)} end end end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() w2 = w/2 h2 = h/2
--Reticle screen.setColor(0, 255, 0, 128) screen.drawCircle(w2, h2, h/3)
--Orientation s_hdg = string.format("%0.0f", (hdg*-360+360)%360) s_elv = string.format("%0.0f", elv*360)
screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) screen.drawText(w2-7, 1, "HDG") screen.drawText(w2-7, 7, s_hdg)
screen.drawText(w2-7, h-12, "ELEV") screen.drawText(w2-7, h-6, s_elv)
--Draws Radar Targets for i, v in pairs(targets) do if v.dist < rng then x = w2 + h * v.az * fov y = h2 + h * (v.elv+elv) * fov r = (rng - v.dist) / rng * 255 screen.setColor(r,0,0) screen.drawRect(x-4,y-4,8,8) end end
--Status screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) if dep then if arm and blink then screen.setColor(255, 0, 0) screen.drawText(1, 1, "ARM") elseif not arm then screen.drawText(1, 1, "RDY") end
screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) if blink and not man then screen.drawText(1, 7, "AUTO") elseif man then screen.drawText(1, 7, "MAN") end else screen.setColor(0, 0, 0) screen.drawClear() screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) screen.drawText(1, 1, "STOW") end end

object.script:
lvl=0 -- Fuel Level cap=0 -- Fuel Capacity spd=0 -- Speed (used to calculate range) min_spd=0.1 draw_mile=false -- Show Milage keypress=true showt=120 --Number of Ticks the milage is shown when in LOW mode it=0 a=64 --Fuel Level Color Intensity
mile=0 mile_txt="" -- Milage last_lvl=0 deltaDB={} dur_txt="" -- Endurance rng_txt="" -- Range
avgi=1 -- Sample Index
function onTick()
lvl = input.getNumber(1) cap = input.getNumber(2) spd = input.getNumber(3) avg = input.getNumber(4) low = input.getNumber(5) / 100
pressa = input.getBool(1) pressb = input.getBool(2) tmr = input.getBool(3) --TRUE when timer hits 1s unit= input.getBool(4) --FALSE: km, TRUE: nm
f = lvl / cap
if spd > min_spd then draw_rng = true else draw_rng = false end
if (pressa or pressb) and keypress then keypress = false draw_mile = not draw_mile --FALSE: no milage, TRUE: milage + fuel content it = 0 elseif not pressa and not pressb then keypress = true end it=it+1
-- Endurance & Range calculation if tmr then if last_lvl > 0 then
-- Fills the list up to a maxium of delta values table.insert(deltaDB, 1, last_lvl - lvl) if #deltaDB > avg then table.remove(deltaDB) end
-- Calculates average delta = deltaDB[1] for i, d in ipairs(deltaDB) do delta = delta + d end delta = delta / (#deltaDB+1)
dur_txt = "" -- Hides endurance, when there is no fuel flow
if delta > 0 then -- Skips if there isn't any fuel consumption
-- Endurance dur = lvl / delta if dur > 3600 then dur_txt = "E:" .. string.format("%.f", dur / 3600) .. "h" elseif dur > 60 then dur_txt = "E:" .. string.format("%.f", dur / 60) .. "m" else dur_txt = "E:" .. string.format("%.f", dur) .. "s" end
-- Milage Calculation if spd > min_spd then --Skips if no Speed if (mile == 0 or input.getBool(5)) and spd > 0 then mile = delta / spd else mile = (mile + delta / spd) / 2 end
-- Range rng = spd * dur if unit then rng = rng / 1852 rng_txt = "R:" .. string.format("%.f", rng) .. "nm" mile_txt = string.format("%.f", mile * 1852) .. "/nm" output.setNumber(3, mile * 1852) else rng = rng / 1000 rng_txt = "R:" .. string.format("%.f", rng) .. "km" mile_txt = string.format("%.f", mile * 1000) .. "/km" output.setNumber(3, mile * 1000) end end end end last_lvl = lvl end
output.setNumber(1, dur) output.setNumber(2, rng) end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() w2 = w / 2 h2 = h / 2
-- Draw tank screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawRect(0,0, w-1, h2) -- draws box
screen.setColor(0, 0, 0) screen.drawLine(0,0,w,0) -- removes lid
r = (1-f) * a g = f * a x = f * (h2 - 1) screen.setColor(r, g, 0) screen.drawRectF(1, h2, w-2, -x) -- fills box
screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) if lvl > 10000 then -- defining text alignment offset x = -8 elseif lvl > 1000 then x = -3 elseif lvl > 100 then x = 2 elseif lvl > 10 then x = 7 else x = 12 end
if f < low and it > showt then draw_mile=false y = 2 screen.setColor(255, 255, 0) screen.drawRectF(w2-9, 8, 18, 7) screen.setColor(0, 0, 0) screen.drawText(w2-7, 9, "LOW") screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) elseif draw_mile and draw_rng then -- Adjusts draw height of Level Text acc. to milage drawn y = 2 screen.drawText(2, 8, mile_txt) else y = h2/2-2 end
screen.drawText(x, y, string.format("%0.1f", lvl) .. "V")
-- Draws Endurance & Range screen.drawText(1, h2+2, dur_txt) if draw_rng then screen.drawText(1, h2+8, rng_txt) end
end

max_range = pN("Max Range (m)") -- 6km max range la_min_range = pN("Land Attack Min Range (m)") ashm_min_range = pN("AShM Min Range (m)")
launch_time = 2*60 zoom = 5 speed = 1 function inrect(x,y,x0,y0,x_l,y_l,bool) return bool and x>=x0 and y>=y0 and y<=y0+y_l and x<=x0+x_l end function pretty(x, deci) return string.format("%."..tostring(deci).."f", x) end function reset() ssC(255,255,255) end function clamp(x,a,b) return math.max(a,math.min(x,b)) end function onTick() w = iN(1) h = iN(2) t1x = iN(3) t1y = iN(4) kx = iN(5) ky = iN(6) gpsx = iN(7) gpsy = iN(8) pressed = iB(1) dist = math.sqrt((gpsx-kx)^2+(gpsy-ky)^2) oN(1,mode-1) for i=1,#cells do oB(i,cells[i]==0) end empty = true for i=1,#cells,1 do if cells[i] >= 0 then empty = false end end if empty then status_code = 3 else if dist > max_range then status_code = 5 elseif (mode == 2 and dist < ashm_min_range) or (mode == 1 and dist < la_min_range) then status_code = 4 else status_code = 1 end end for i=1,#cells,1 do if cells[i] >= 1 and cells[i] < launch_time then cells[i] = cells[i] + 1 status_code = 2 elseif cells[i] == launch_time then cells[i] = -1 status_code = 1 end end oN(2,zoom) oN(3, status_code) oN(4,speed) end

box_width = w/2 sdR(w/4-1,h/2,box_width+1,h/2-1) -- frame sdL(w/4+box_width/2-1,h/2,w/4+box_width/2-1,h) -- dividing lines sdL(w/4+2*box_width/2,h/2,w/4+2*box_width/2,h) sdL(w/4-1,3*h/4-1,w/4+w/2,3*h/4-1) for i=1,4,1 do if cells[i]==0 then ssC(0,255,0,96) elseif cells[i] == -1 then ssC(255,0,0,96) else if math.floor(cells[i]/10)%2==0 then ssC(255,255,0,96) else ssC(255,255,0,64) end end sdRF(w/4+((i-1)%2)*(box_width/2), h/2+(h/4)*(math.floor((i-1)/2)), box_width/2, h/4-1) reset() sdTB(w/4+((i-1)%2)*(box_width/2), h/2+(h/4)*(math.floor((i-1)/2)), box_width/2, h/4-1,tostring(i),0,0) if inrect(t1x,t1y, w/4+((i-1)%2)*(box_width/2), h/2+(h/4)*(math.floor((i-1)/2)), box_width/2, h/4-1, pressed) and cells[i]==0 and status_code==1 then cells[i] = 1 end end

tx = 0 ty = 0 ogx = 0 -- original launch coordinates ogy = 0 nc = 5 -- """nav constant""" tilt_target = 0 -- forward pitch tilt
mode = 0 death = false -- Destroyer of worlds redirect = false alt_hold = true drop_self = false
function clamp(x,a,b) return math.min(b, math.max(a, x)) end
function onTick() ix = iN(1) iy = iN(2) m = iN(3) gx = iN(4) gy = iN(5) c = iN(6) alt = iN(7) tilt = iN(8) rad_dist = iN(9) terminal = pN("(LA) Terminal Distance") red_elev = pN("(LA) Redirector Elevation") alt_height = pN("(LA) Alt Hold Height") ashm_alt_0 = pN("(AShM) Terminal Altitude") ashm_alt_1 = pN("(AShM) Approach Altitude") ashm_alt_2 = pN("(AShM) Intermediate Cruise Altitude") ashm_alt_3 = pN("(AShM) Primary Cruise Altitude") launched = iB(1) if ix ~= 0 or iy ~= 0 then tx = ix ty = iy mode = m ogx = ix ogy = iy ogd = math.sqrt((tx-gx)^2+(ty-gy)^2) end tv = ((math.atan(tx - gx, ty - gy) / pi2 + c)%1 + 1.5)%1 - 0.5 d = math.sqrt((tx-gx)^2+(ty-gy)^2) if launched and mode == 0 then -- LAND ATTACK: High altitude cruise, top attack if alt >= red_elev then redirect = true tilt_target = -0.25 -- for later... end if d <= terminal and not death then death = true alt_hold = false drop_self = true end if not death then oN(1, clamp(tv*nc,-1,1)) -- yaw else oN(1, 0) end if death and tilt <= -0.2 then drop_self = false end oN(2, d) oN(3, clamp(alt+5,100,alt_height)) -- gradually set alt hold height (land attack only) oN(4, tilt_target) -- set target for missile pitch (land attack only)

if death and rad_dist > 0 then oN(1, 0) -- disable GPS guidance when target is within range else oN(1, clamp(tv*nc,-1,1)) -- yaw end oN(2, d) oB(3, alt_hold) oB(1, death) oB(2, redirect) else oN(1, 0) oN(2, 0) oB(1, false) oB(2, false) oB(3, false) oB(4, false) end end
